1) Weigh your ingredients! Including liquids and solids.
2) Don't use baking soda older than 6 months after opening.
3) After forming the cookie dough into rounds, place in the fridge for 24 hours to let the flavors meld.
4) Put some rock salt on top of the cookie to help even out the sweetness.
5) Consider substituting ALL of the white sugar for brown sugar.
6) Consider substituting half of the all purpose flour for cake flour for a softer cookie with a finer crumb.
7) Consider weighing the cookie dough rounds for consistency.
